        <body>       
                 
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p><del>609 WALNUT STREET&#44;<lb/>
                PHILADELPHIA.</del><lb/></p>
            <p>Blue Mt. Lake<lb/>
                Adirondacks. N.Y.<lb/>
                Aug 25<hi rend="sup">th</hi> &#39;87.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev &#38; Dear Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>I hope you will<lb/> pardon the liberty I take<lb/> in seeking your aid upon no<lb/> warrant but that of fellow&#45;<lb/>citizenship &#38; our common worship<lb/> of &#34;the one Universal Father.&#34;<lb/></p>
            <p>I have been&#44; for some time&#44;<lb/> desirous of becoming a thorough<lb/> student of the Hebrew Scriptures<lb/> in the original &#38; wanted&#44; very<lb/> much&#44; last winter to study<lb/> under a faith&#45;full &#34;teacher<lb/> in Israel&#34;; but&#44; even as it was&#44;<lb/></p> 
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I attempted too much&#59; &#38; the<lb/> result is that I shall<lb/> probably have to go west to<lb/> get rid of an obstinate case<lb/> of bronchitis.  And so I wish<lb/> to learn of someone near whom&#44;<lb/> or with whom&#44; I could live &#38;<lb/> give all my indoor time to<lb/> study.  For <hi rend="underline">climate</hi>&#44; I should<lb/> probably prefer New Mexico<lb/> or Colorado&#44;&#45;&#45;or perhaps California<lb/> <hi rend="underline">Southern</hi> California.<lb/></p>
            <p>I had the pleasure of a little<lb/> interview with Dr. Mendes&#44; re&#45;<lb/>cently in New York.  He told<lb/> me of a Rev. M. De Solla&#45;&#45;<lb/> Denver&#44; Col.&#45;&#45;&#40;a liberal&#44; how&#45;<lb/>ever&#41;; &#38; this was the only person<lb/> he knew of in the west.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>A young man from California&#44; who happened to<lb/> come in&#44; knew of an earnest &#38; enthusiastic man<lb/> in Los Angeles&#44; but could not give his name.<lb/></p>  
            <p>Dr. Mendes advised me to turn to you&#44; as a<lb/> fellow townsman&#44; &#38; this I do the more readily&#44;<lb/> having heard not only of your erudition&#44; which<lb/> the university has recognized&#44; but&#45;&#45;what is<lb/> higher than that&#45;&#45;of your staunch adherence<lb/> to the faith of your fathers.  And that is what<lb/> I especially want in a teacher in the west.<lb/>  In these days&#44; when the ancient scriptures are<lb/> being so questioned&#44; as to date&#44; authorship &#38;c&#45;&#45; &#40;&#38;<lb/></p> 
                
                <pb n="4"/>
            <p>correctly so far as those without<lb/> <hi rend="underline">exact</hi> knowledge can tell&#41;&#44; I<lb/> need one who can help me<lb/> with both knowledge &#38; faith.<lb/></p>
            <p>My eventual object is either<lb/> the ministry of my own church&#44;<lb/> &#45;&#45;<hi rend="underline">or</hi> the work of college professor.<lb/></p>
            <p>Any help you can give me<lb/> will be heartily appreciated<lb/> by<lb/> Yours very truly&#44;<lb/> <hi rend="underline">J. P. Hubbard</hi>. Jr.<lb/></p>
            <p>Address will be<lb/> next week&#58;&#45;&#45;care W. M. Goosoenot<lb/> Caldwell. Lake George. N. Y.<lb/></p>
            <p>thereafter&#58;&#45;&#45;Cotnit. Cape Cod.<lb/> Mass.<lb/></p>
            </body>
